The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Pakistan want India to play Twenty20

Islamabad: Following the huge success of the Twenty20 Cup domestic matches in Lahore last month, the PCB is considering playing international ties in the format against India and England when they visit here next season. England are scheduled to tour Pakistan from October 22 while India are proposed to play from January 2, next year. Both teams will play three Tests and five ODIs each in Pakistan. 

After the interest the Twenty20 cup evoked last month, we are not averse to playing Twenty20 matches against England and India on the coming tours, PCB director board operations Abbas Zaidi said in a local daily. (PTI) 




